      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">19.1508</ph> Contract clauses.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d1255e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1285e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1285e15" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        The contracting officer shall insert the clause <xref href="FAR-i1057902.dita#i1057902"
                              base="i1057902"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.219-29</xref>, Notice of Set-Aside for, or Sole Source Award to, Economically Disadvantaged Women-owned Small Business Concerns, in solicitations and contracts for acquisitions that are set aside for,Â or awarded on a sole source basis to, EDWOSB concerns under <xref href="FAR-i1099249.dita#i1099249"
                              base="i1099249"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.1505</xref>(b) or <xref href="FAR-i1099284.dita#i1099284"
                              base="i1099284"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.1506</xref>(a). This includes multiple-award contracts when orders may be set aside for EDWOSB concerns as described in <xref href="FAR-i1117805.dita#i1117805"
                              base="i1117805"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">8.405-5</xref> and <xref href="FAR-i1104008.dita#i1104008"
                              base="i1104008"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">16.505</xref>(b)(2)(i)(F) or when orders may be issued directly to one EDWOSB contractor in accordance with <xref href="FAR-19.504.dita#id203CEK0I0HS"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.504</xref>(c)(1)(ii).
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1285e39" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        For contracts that are set aside, the contracting officer shall indicate in paragraph (e) of the clause whether compliance with the limitations on subcontracting is required at the contract level or order level.
                     </p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1285e44" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1285e49" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        The contracting officer shall insert the clause <xref href="FAR-i1057947.dita#i1057947"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.219-30</xref>, Notice of Set-Aside for, or Sole Source Award to, Women-Owned Small Business Concerns Eligible Under the Women-Owned Small Business Program, in solicitations and contracts for acquisitions that are set aside for, or awarded on a sole source basis to, WOSB concerns under <xref href="FAR-i1099249.dita#i1099249"
                              base="i1099249"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.1505</xref>(c) or <xref href="FAR-i1099284.dita#i1099284"
                              base="i1099284"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.1506</xref>(b). This includes multiple-award contracts when orders may be set aside for WOSB concerns eligible under the WOSB program as described in <xref href="FAR-i1117805.dita#i1117805"
                              base="i1117805"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">8.405-5</xref> and <xref href="FAR-i1104008.dita#i1104008"
                              base="i1104008"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">16.505</xref>(b)(2)(i)(F) or when orders may be issued directly to one WOSB contractor in accordance with <xref href="FAR-19.504.dita#id203CEK0I0HS"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.504</xref>(c)(1)(ii).
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1285e73" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        For contracts that are set aside, the contracting officer shall indicate in paragraph (e) of the clause whether compliance with the limitations on subcontracting is required at the contract level or order level.
                     </p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
